-- PGE Opens 1.25 Billion-Zloty Tender for Nuclear Plant Adviser in Poland
-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 2011-02-07T06:26:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-07/pge-opens-1-25-billion-zloty-tender-for-nuclear-plant-adviser-in-poland.html
PGE EJ 1, the nuclear power unit of  Poland ’s biggest utility PGE SA, has opened a tender for a 10-
year, 1.25 billion-zloty ($437.6 million) contract to provide
technical advisory services as owner’s engineer in the
construction of a 3,000-megawatt nuclear power plant, the
company said in an e-mail late yesterday.  The PGE unit also announced a 120 million-zloty tender for
advisory services to help determine the plant’s location and
environmental impact and to obtain the necessary regulatory
permits.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid at 
 dmcquaid1@bloomberg.net  